			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: FM and LDON hards<a name="67238"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 17 04 4:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you're good you'll only need a couple fades in an entire hard...the key is: don't be afraid to pull 2...just mes one on the way back then remes it once it gets to camp.  If there's more than two, lull 1, pull 2...if you get more than that(which is rare except on those horrible rooms with 50 mobs) just mes some while running away then fade once your down to two mobs.  This way, you're only fading if you have a critical lull resist or if you have 3-4+ mobs on you.
<br />

<br />
And always leave plenty of room between you and your group.
<br />

<br />
The more mana the better, same with FT...but someone with only enough mana for 2 fades and 0 FT could do it once they got the hang of it...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">~<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=288060" target="_blank" class="postlink">Impresario Lendias Silvertune</a><br>
