				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: FM and LDON hards<a name="67250"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 17 04 8:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>With VoQ my mana pool just barely tops 4900 so  I can get 5 fades in a row before I run out of mana and with my my mana regen at a pathetic 12/ tick I need that bigger mana pool.  As mentioned, if you do it right it's easier to just pull 2 and mezz one.  With the new Lull at 66 Hards are a lot easier to pull but it doesn't reduce the agro range, just the range at wich mobs will assist, great for pulling singles but doesn't help with those rooms where the mobs are hidden right behind a door.
<br />

<br />
So, short answer, the more mana and FT you have the better but if you're quick with the mezzes you shouldn't have any trouble pulling.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
