				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: FM and LDON hards<a name="67256"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 17 04 11:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In fact, I dont &quot;mez one on the way back&quot;... I mez one, pull the other, and just know the add is coming 3 ticks behind.  I have found this tactic handy in OOW as well.  I was in Ruined City of Dranik today.  Some of the mobs were unlullable but mezzable.  mezz, switch, debuff, slow, buff, buff, switch mezz, switch... not tough but group was cheering my name.
<br />

<br />
Just standard LDON hard technique for me.  2 targets together and I dont trust lull.. mezz one to aggro the other.  If they arent close enough to aggro on a mezz, you are just gonna get the one a little later (bellow to break mezz)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
