				<td colspan="2"><span>Mez is generally a great exploratory tool when you are in a new place.  You might not be able to see all the mobs that will assist, and you dont want to take the time to send in the eye and scout about.
<br />

<br />
I generally just drop a mez on the mob i can see and see what happens.  If just one add comes I will take it to group and, depending on toughness of mob, either fade off the mezzed one or wait for it to break and mez it as it comes running in.  If more come than I can handle, just fade.
<br />

<br />
It's a lazy way but requires little or no brain and a fades worth of mana for dire screwup.  
<br />

<br />
I rarely lull now especially when pulling outdoors. Just run around like an idiot with 4 evil mobs chasing me mezzing till i can handle the remainder, take em back and fade the unwanted. 
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
