				<td colspan="2"><span>The right one will agro to assist the middle one, as often as not.  Prox agro and mez agro can be smaller but the differences are minor.  I've seen differences between tagging with bellow versus tagging with HOS, too.  If you can agro a single with proximity, the assist radius is noticeably smaller than with spells, but whether you could do what you describe or not, I do not know.  I have never seen three mobs with overlapping assist radii where you get the second one on assist and don't get the third assisting the second.  But that's just my experience. No hard data to back that up.</span></td>
