				<td colspan="2"><span>I recently went through this learning curve and here is what I found.
<br />

<br />
I NEVER do a hard without a chanter. Their mezz is just that much better than ours. They can typicly mezz higher levels of mobs that us, and they dont need to re-mezz every minute.
<br />

<br />
I use fade about two to three times per hard ldon. I find that the mana regen is usually not an issue. I frequently bring back two or even three to the group, mez one myself, chanter mezzes one and the tank aggros the third.. then chanter mezzes mine. Sometimes I die because the tank is not fast enough .. but no biggie.. I never do a hard without a cleric either.
<br />

<br />
The only time I really need fade is when I have either a room full of mobs ... or several un mezzable (or suspected-unmezzable i.e. red or yellow) mobs in an area.
<br />

<br />
All I ususally use for aggro is proximity aggro. I used to think this was wrong but I get much fewer adds whith prox aggro.</span></td>
