				<td colspan="2"><span>OK one correction for donvanlot.. max level is 57 on the 64 charm... 
<br />

<br />
And yes spoogy, to level 58 bards charm is still pretty good.  But even now its tapering off.  The highest level mob you can charm at 58 is a level 51 mob.  In groups you are fighting fewer of those now.  As you level from here that cap will not go up until you hit 64.  
<br />

<br />
A level 63 bard thats killing level 51 mobs is bottom feeding.  There is no way you will use charm in a group of similar level folks.  They will want to hunt bigger, better prey. So charm is a soloing tool only at that point.  At 64 it goes up to level 57 mobs, but the issue remains, groups will want to hunt level 60+ mobs, charming is for solo.  Enchanters, druids and necros all charm better than us for groups in the 60s.
<br />

<br />
But as I said, you might have said mezz and been right on it.  I feel, for exactly your reasoning, that bards are superior to enchanters for most mezzing duties.  The only trouble is, each additional lockdown takes away another bard benefit.  Wo when I pull I am aiming to park the inc mob on the MAs head... mezzed, and help finish of the prior target within 3 ticks of arrival.  I love force feeding tanks.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
