			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: FM and LDON hards<a name="67515"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 19 04 7:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Like others here, I prefer the mez+pull method.
<br />

<br />
My variant (if it is one) is to snare the mob that has woken up somewhere between the place I put him to sleep and the group so I can control his placement.  In that way, no one gets hit and I can twist and target toggle mez at the same time.
<br />

<br />
On 3 pulls, I will mez one, mez a 2nd on the run back to the group, leave the remaining mob with the group, go back and remez the 2nd mob, wait for 1st mob to wake up, bring it close to group, mez it, wait for 2nd mob to wake up, snare it and bring it close to group.
<br />

<br />
One thing to remember.  Just because a mob didn't aggro his friends when you mezzed him, doesn't mean that he won't aggro his friends when he wakes up.  Now, I am not positive that this occurs simply because mez doesn't cause as big of an aggro radius or odd pathing after the mob wakes up may cause additional aggros.  Whatever the case, don't assume a single mezzed mob will come back to the group as a single mezzed mob.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Leamhanach
66-82 Half-Elf Bard</span></td>
