			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: FM and LDON hards<a name="67552"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 7:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you lull a mob, then mezz the guy next to him... then that mezz wears off AFTER the lull does both will come running if they're social and within range of each other.  The moment the mezzed mob regains control of himself and runs after you he'll bring mobs within his agro radius who aren't lulled.  That's probably what you're experiencing.
<br />

<br />
I used to pull with snare and in rare circumstances I still do but generally full run speed mobs are more condusive to my style of chain pulling.  I do like to have them mezzed and ready to go though when their predicessor drops.
<br />

<br />
I did have opportunity to pull with Snare the other day when, after a server reset, both the Kyv Assasin and his Noc named counterpart were standing outside the Tendonslicer Hut and neither could be mezzed or lulled.  I snared one, both agroed, the unsnared one ran to my group and I faded so the Assasin just wandered back to his post while we killed his buddy.  I've had occasion to do that with other mobs when I needed to pull a named out of a congested area for example, snare the named and lead the rest of the pack away while the MT tags the named, etc.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><img src="http://www.geetronics.com/liis4.jpg"><hr>
